		<td><b>Re: Tablet PC Settings Missing in Windows 7</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In the Windows registry, open HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Desktop and change MenuDropAlignment back to 0.<br /><br />Source: <a href="http://www.pctools.com/guides/registry/detail/340/" class="postlink">PCTools.com</a> via Google <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">windows menu alignment registry</tt>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


